The paper proposes a differentiable approximation of the top-k operator, which is widely used in machine learning and data mining. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions applications to k-nearest neighbors and beam search algorithms, which are commonly used in data science and information theory, respectively. Therefore, the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) are also likely candidates.
